# Users

SREs under pressure, developers debugging, ops managing pipelines/retention. The UI must serve all three: fast search, clear configuration, readable logs.

# Design principles

1. **Instrument, not dashboard** — each view has a focused purpose; avoid metric clutter.
2. **Quiet until needed** — calm default; color/motion/emphasis only when meaningful.
3. **Typography is the interface** — four-level hierarchy (bright → normal → muted → ghost); prefer type over chrome.
4. **Respect the palette** — semantic colors only; **no raw hex**; use design tokens.
5. **Crafted details** — scrollbars, resize handles, focus rings, grain, etc. matter.
